{
  "texts": [
    "Modern economies depend on a vast web of production and distribution networks that move materials and goods around the world.",
    "Each link in these networks represents a dependency for inputs, logistics, and market access.",
    "The efficiency of global supply chains has enabled remarkable gains in productivity and specialization.",
    "Yet the same interdependence has also created structural fragilities that become visible only when disruptions occur.",
    "Events such as the COVID-19 pandemic, the semiconductor shortage, or the war in Ukraine have revealed how localized disturbances can cascade through multiple tiers of suppliers, amplifying their effects until entire sectors or regions experience economic stress 1, 2."
  ]
}